/title Hive5: 2-minute concept check
/paragraph We’re exploring an easier way for neighbors to share tools & gear instead of everyone buying rarely used items. Your quick feedback helps us decide what to build next. Responses are anonymous unless you add email at the end.

/title Have you ever borrowed or lent a tool or piece of equipment with a neighbor or friend?
/multiple
- Yes, borrowed
- Yes, lent
- Both
- No

/title What kinds of things would you consider sharing (or borrowing)?
/multi-select
- Yard tools (mowers, trimmers, blowers)
- Power tools (drills, saws, sanders)
- Outdoor / event gear (tents, tables, coolers)
- Sports or hobby gear (bikes, kayaks, cameras)
- Something else — add below
/long Optional: What else would you share?

/title If there were an easy app to find and borrow items nearby, how interested would you be?
/multiple
- Very interested
- Somewhat interested
- Neutral
- Not really interested
- Not at all interested

/title What would make you hesitate to use it?
/multi-select
- Trust or safety concerns
- Worry about damage or theft
- Too much hassle
- Don’t think neighbors would participate
- Other — add below
/short Optional: Other hesitation

/title If Hive5 helped you save money and reduce clutter, how valuable would that be to you?
/multiple
- Extremely valuable
- Somewhat valuable
- Neutral
- Not valuable

/title If Hive5 offered optional per-rental insurance, would that make you more likely to use it?
/multiple
- Yes
- Maybe
- No

/title Would you like an invite when a local beta launches?
/multiple
- Yes, I’d like early access
- Maybe — tell me more first
- No thanks

/title What’s your ZIP code?
/short
/title Your email (optional, for invite)
/email

/logic If [Would you like an invite…] is [Yes, I’d like early access] or [Maybe — tell me more first] THEN [Show blocks: ZIP + Email]
/logic If [Would you like an invite…] is [No thanks] THEN [Hide blocks: ZIP + Email]

